        </cite>
      </blockquote>
      <p>
        This page lists all the creative bots I've made (<a href="#active-bots">{{active_bots_count}} active</a>,
        <a href="#inactive-bots">{{inactive_bots_count}} inactive</a>, {{bots_count_total}} in total), with <a
          href="https://stefanbohacek.com/blog/analyzing-fediverse-followers/">thousands of unique followers</a> (9,129 as of November 6, 2025) across
        all of them. If you want to learn more about creative botmaking, and maybe even make your
        own bot, here's a few links to get you started:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://botwiki.org/">Botwiki</a>, an online encyclopedia of creative bots and a collection of
          resources for making them, including the <a
            href="https://botwiki.org/resource/guide/the-definitive-guide-to-creative-botmaking/">Definitive Guide to
            Creative Botmaking</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          the <a href="https://botmakers.org/">Botmakers</a> Discourse group
        </li>
        <li>
          tutorials and descriptions of my bot projects <a href="https://stefanbohacek.com/tag/bots/">on my blog</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          and you might also enjoy my <a
            href="https://stefanbohacek.com/blog/twitter-bots-a-retrospective/">retrospective on Twitter bots</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Be sure to check out my other projects <a href="https://stefanbohacek.com/">on my personal website</a>, and follow me <a href="https://stefanbohacek.online/@stefan" rel="me">on Mastodon</a>. And here's how you can <a
